### Key Terms and Definitions  

| Term                  | Definition                                                                                                          |
|-----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Function              | A reusable block of code that performs a specific task when called.                                                 |
| Method                | A function associated (bound) with an object or data structure (e.g., string methods or array methods).              |
| Parameter             | A variable in a function definition representing an input.                                                           |
| Argument              | The actual value passed to a function when called.                                                                  |
| Arrow Function        | A shorter syntax for writing functions, introduced in ES6, often used for concise function expressions.              |
| Callback Function     | A function passed as an argument to another function and executed inside it.                                         |
| Higher-Order Function | A function that takes one or more functions as arguments or returns a function as a result.                          |
| `forEach`             | Array method to execute a function for each element without returning a new array.                                   |
| `map`                 | Array method that creates a new array by applying a function to each element of the original array.                  |
| `filter`              | Array method that creates a new array with elements passing a test specified by a callback function.                  |
| `reduce`              | Array method that reduces an array to a single value by applying a reducer function cumulatively to elements.       |
| Scope                 | The region of the code where a variable is accessible (parameters have function/block scope).                         |
| Redundancy            | Repetition of code which is minimized by using functions for cleaner, maintainable code.                             |

